WEBVTT

00:05:30.433 --> 00:05:31.709
And one more thing.

00:05:31.733 --> 00:05:34.643
And as an educator, this is the one
that really bothers me:

00:05:34.667 --> 00:05:36.843
If argument is war,

00:05:36.867 --> 00:05:41.876
then there's an implicit equation
of learning with losing.

00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:43.507
And let me explain what I mean.

00:05:44.067 --> 00:05:46.609
Suppose you and I have an argument.

00:05:46.633 --> 00:05:49.633
You believe a proposition, P, and I don't.

00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:52.414
And I say, "Well, why do you believe P?"

00:05:52.438 --> 00:05:53.843
And you give me your reasons.

00:05:53.867 --> 00:05:56.243
And I object and say,
"Well, what about ...?"

00:05:56.267 --> 00:05:57.776
And you answer my objection.

00:05:57.800 --> 00:06:00.209
And I have a question:
"Well, what do you mean?